channel.title: WAMP5 Help
channel.description:
Well, I've installed it, but it seems like the services haven't istalled. :X
So, I opened up the taskbar menu and attempted to install the services and no cigar still :X Seems apache is the only thing not starting. (1 service runs and then stops I guess because the other isn't working)
Has anyone else had this problem?

item.title: WAMP5 Help
item.dc:creator: @Pwnd Pwnd
item.description:
@Pwnd wrote:

;O

Well, it was true that apache didn’t install correctly, but I uninstalled, restarted and reinstalled and it was fine

Some firewall issues could have fhkd with that too.

Thanks guys.

item.dc:creator: @Bang_Train Bang Train
item.description:
@Bang_Train wrote:

also check no mysql-nt or anything similar sounding is running in taskmanager same for apache

if they run shut them down by ending the process and try installing the process again

also pache is REALLY slow to start some times so give it a few mins
